In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. acknowledges the devastating impact of Alzheimer's disease on millions of Americans and their loved ones. He highlights the need for improved treatment and a cure for this common form of dementia. The economic toll of Alzheimer's is also mentioned, with treatment costs exceeding $300 billion in 2020. President Biden proposes the funding of a new program called the Advanced Research Projects Agency for Health (ARPA-H) to accelerate research on detecting, treating, and curing diseases like Alzheimer's. He also emphasizes the importance of addressing health disparities and ensuring that marginalized communities, such as older Black and Brown Americans who are disproportionately affected by Alzheimer's, are included in prevention and treatment efforts. The article recognizes the dedication and sacrifices of caregivers, especially during the COVID-19 pandemic, and mentions the investment of $145 million from the American Rescue Plan to support caregivers. President Biden calls for continued support and care for those affected by Alzheimer's until a cure is found.